This is verbatim from HAKMEM, and unless I miss the point of this post, it's
not that hard...
It's one of those little tricks that comes from indexed address arithmetic.

ITEM 165 (Freiberg):
A byte pointer can be converted to a character address < 2^18 by MULI A,<#
bytes/word> followed by SUBI B,1-<# b/w>(A). To get full word character
address, use SUB into a magic table.

Sarr J. Blumson <sarr@stick.us.itd.umich.edu> wrote in message
