I was commenting on the edit history that was posted.
I originally stated that I didn't know if there was 
a tape available for customers to get it by "honest"
means.  A lot of stuff was carried into customer sites
and left there under the table, depending on the customer's
needs.  I do know that Magee never built a BLISS tape (she
would have been complaining to me for hundreds of hours).
So that means that a tape wasn't submitted to SDC from
1976 or 1977 on.  I also do know that, even though a 
release of Bliss-10 was highly desirable (this was in 1982),
the logistics of doing a release ala the Project Notebook
was impossible.

One of the things that I started, was a formal review of
the SDC paperwork with each monitor release.  A part of that
review involved going over all of the SPDs to assess the
impact and, more importantly, the deimpact of anything
that would affect the tape submission.  I don't recall
seeing a Bliss SPD.

/BAH

