DEC invested money in replacing F40 with FORTRAN-10/20 because the
customers said it was necessary (just like those TU7x's).  The last I
heard, FORTRAN-10/20 had the highest PDP-10 market penetration of any
DEC layered product.

A product like FORTRAN-10/20 couldn't have been developed for nearly the
same cost in people, time and money without some implementation language
like BLISS-10.  What BLISS substitutes were already available on the -10
in the early 70's?
				/AHM
