perhaps among other places.


>... (there were a number of GETSEGs).

Nope.  I've seen BLISS-36 run with multiple hisegs (named BLSSG1 through
BLSSG4, I think); perhaps only on TOPS-10, since
http://pdp-10.trailing-edge.com/pdp-10/BB-J939F-BM.HTML
only builds a single-hiseg BLISS-36.

However, BLISS-10 does not have multiple hisegs.


> Neither of these BLISSes were shipped with sources ...

The place Timothy Stark subsequently found BLISS-10 (``TOPS-20 V3A 2020
DISTRIBUTION TAPE 9 TRACK 1600 BPI MAGTAPE DRIVE# 273 S/N 2 SYS,
BB-D868B-BM''
http://pdp-10.trailing-edge.com/pdp-10/BB-D868B-BM_TOPS20_V3A_2020_DIST.html )

was the latest version, V7E(227), and it contains all the sources.

I still don't recall how TOPS-10 sites got BLISS-10 sources, but we
certainly had them in the field.
